The paper deals with the impact of channel state misreporting on multi-user scheduling performance in massive MIMO systems. This involves analyzing the sensitivity of scheduling performance to channel misreporting, which is a key issue in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the impact of misreporting on system throughput and user rates, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper focuses on massive MIMO systems, which is a subfield of wireless communications (cs.MM) and involves the use of large antenna arrays to improve system performance. Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis and modeling to derive results, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG).
